August 17 -- USA 15km Race Walking Championships

Thirty two race walkers started, contesting several events all in one race.

The weather was clear and 65 degrees at the start, but the sun quickly took temperatures to the upper 70s.

 

Highlights:

Sherry Watts, of Ontario Canada, set a Canadian age group record of 1:35:40 for the 15km Race Walk.

Kristen Furseth, of Okemos MI, walked 20km in 1:46:15, achieving the qualifying standard for elite competition in 2009.

Patrick Stroupe, of Armstrong MO, looked incredibly smooth and easy as he walked away from everyone, finishing 15km in 1:10:26. He completed the first 5km in 21:56!

Stephanie Casey, of Des Moines IA, was not far behind in 1:17:52 for 15km. She completed the first 5km in 24:57.

 

Photographer: Gary Westlund    Pictures Pictures Pictures

 

Race Walking Judges: Joan Grossman (chief), Ginger Mulanax, Diane Graham-Henry, Don DeNoon, Jo Burrows, Cheryl Sunman, Sandra DeNoon

Recorder: Lauren Hill

Judging Summary Sheet (pdf)

 

Timing: Championchip Minnesota

Timer: Jim Hewitt

Backup Timer: Steve Hyland

 

Course: USATF Course Certification Number MN-07034-RR

Location: Midtown Greenway Trail, Minneapolis, MN
